    <p>BOB BISHOP: You take the farmer off the tractor, that's going to be quite the change. And what markets will be out there, who knows?</p>
    <p>WHITES-KODITSCHEK: The Bishops love to farm and are looking to solar to help them stay on the land. They lease about 650 acres, about a third of their land, to what will be one of the Midwest largest solar projects. Twenty-nine-year-old Andrew Bishop wants to raise a family here and have something to pass along.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF ENGINE STARTING)</p>
