    <p>LUNDEN: But one of Legrand's lifelong loves was jazz. He heard Dizzy Gillespie's big band in Paris after the war and eventually worked with him and with other jazz greats like John Coltrane and Miles Davis.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF MICHEL LEGRAND AND MILES DAVIS' "THE DREAM")</p>
    <p>LUNDEN: Jazz informed some of Legrand's film scores. He collaborated with director Jacques Demy in 1964 on "The Umbrellas Of Cherbourg" in which all of the dialogue is sung.</p>
